                        <summary><p>Gaṅgājaṭādhara temple of Govindapputtūr. On the lowest part of the base of the northern façade; begins on the western side of the <foreign>gomukha</foreign> on the <foreign>ardha-maṇḍapa</foreign> and continues on the <foreign>antarala</foreign>; the last part is on the lowest part of the base of the eastern section of the sanctuary. Regnal year 7 of Kōrājarājakesarivarman = Rājarāja I (<foreign>circa</foreign> 992 C.E.). There is no <foreign>svasti śrī</foreign> at the beginning of this inscription; many passages of this inscription remain illegible, and the translation is thus fragmentary.</p>
                            
                        </summary>
